  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN147.1-kilavi">celavuṇarttiya tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What SHE said to the confidante who informed [her] of [his] going.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN147.1">
              <l><anchor n="1"/>ōṅkumalaic cilampiṟ piṭavuṭaṉ malarnta</l>
              <l>vēṅkai veṟittaḻai vēṟuvakut taṉṉa</l>
              <l>vūṉpoti<anchor n="2"/> yaviḻāk kōṭṭukirk kuruḷai</l>
              <l><supplied>mū</supplied>ṉṟuṭa ṉiṉṟa muṭaṅkar nikaḻnta</l>
              <l>tuṟukal viṭaraḷaip piṇavuppaci kūrnteṉap</l>
              <l>poṟikiḷa ruḻuvaip pēḻvā yēṟṟai</l>
              <l>yaṟukōṭ ṭuḻaimā ṉāṇkura lōrkku</l>
              <l>neṟipaṭu kavalaiya nirampā nīḷiṭai</l>
              <l>veḷḷi vī<supplied>ti</supplied>yaip pōla naṉṟuñ</l>
              <l>celavayarn tataṉāl yāṉē palapulan</l>
              <l>tuṇṇā vuyakkamō ṭuyircelac cāayt</l>
              <l>tōḷun tol<supplied>ka</supplied>viṉ ṟolaiya nāḷum</l>
              <l>pirintōr peyarviṟ kiraṅki</l>
              <l>maruntupiṟi tiṉmaiyi ṉiruntumviṉai yilaṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Because of [his] preparing for departure, (10ab)</l>
                <l>easy like on a silver street, (9)</l>
                <l>on the endless long ways that have crossroads coming in on the path, (8)</l>
                <l>where the stag listens to the voices of men, [its] horns broken (7)</l>
                <l>by the large-mouthed male of the tiger with shining spots, (6)</l>
                <l>because [its] female’s hunger was increasing in the cave in the thick stones (5)</l>
                <l>where lasting exhaustion had befallen all three of them, (4)</l>
                <l>the young ones with curved claws that do not come out of [their] sheaths, (3)</l>
                <l>who are like the perfumed foliage of the kino tree differently arranged (2)</l>
                <l>that flower together with the Piṭavu on the side of the high mountain,</l>
                <l rend="indent4">I, being much vexed (10cd)</l>
                <l>not eating, being exhausted by distress, so that my life will go, (11)</l>
                <l>pining for the return of him who has parted [from me], (13)</l>
                <l>daily, so that the old beauty of [my] shoulders is lost, (12)</l>
                <l>because there is no other remedy, although [still] existing I am without purpose. (14)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

